mission had been granted for the southward\nmovement of 2,000 Nationalist guerrilla troops into Karen\nand Mon territory.\n\nBURMA\n2 NOVEMBER 1955\n\nArea of Karen concentration\nArea of KMT activity\n\nComment\nA movement\nof 2,000 guerrillas would involve approximately half of the Nationalists estimated still in Burma.\nSuch a reinforcement of the Karens would not strengthen\nthem enough to threaten the Rangoon government. The\nBurmese government would undoubtedly hold the United\nStates responsible for its increased difficulties with the insurgents, arguing that they could only be maintained in\nstrength by aid from Thailand and Formosa, which Burmese\nofficials regard as under American guidance.\n\nAlthough Taipei\nhas formally disavowed the\nNationalist irregulars in Burma,\n\npast few weeks revealing the close collaboration of both Bangkok and Taipei with the insurgents", "token_count": 139, "token_end_0based": 138, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "5 chinese nationalist guerrillas may be joining burmese insurgents permission had been granted for the southward movement of 2 000 nationalist guerrilla troops into karen and mon territory burma 2 november 1955 area of karen concentration area of kmt activity comment a movement of 2 000 guerrillas would involve approximately half of the nationalists estimated still in burma such a reinforcement of the karens would not strengthen them enough to threaten the rangoon government the burmese government would undoubtedly hold the united states responsible for its increased difficulties with the insurgents arguing that they could only be maintained in strength by aid from thailand and formosa which burmese officials regard as under american guidance although taipei has formally disavowed the nationalist irregulars in burma past few weeks revealing the close collaboration of both bangkok and taipei with the insurgents", "unred_source_page": 8}
